Additional Readings
The following readings were selected by students as part of their oral
presentations on current events.
Geddes, Linda. "Boy Toy Preference Driven by Hormones. New Scientist (January
9, 2010): 12.
Renkl, Margaret. "Guns and Dolls: Why Boys and Girls Play So Differently, and
Whether You Can (Or Should) Try to Change Them," Parenting.com.
Douglas, Susan J. "Girls_Gone_Anti-Feminist." In These Times Online, Spring
1997.
"Airbrushed_Twiggy_Photo_'Misleading'." BBC News online. December 16, 2009.
Erlanger, Steven. "Point,_Shoot,_Retouch_and_Label?" The New York Times,
December 2, 2009.
Blinder, Alan. "'Judson_Girls'_Like_College's_Nurturing_Environment."
Tuscaloosa News, October 11, 2010.
Williams, Rachel. "Single-Sex_Schools_Help_Boys_to_Enjoy_Arts,_Says_Study." The
Guardian, January 20, 2010.
Dunn, Kathleen. "Biological_Determinism_and_LGBT_Tolerance:_A_Quantitative
Exploration_of_Biopolitical_Beliefs." Western Journal of Black Studies 34, no.
3 (Fall 2010): 367.
Nordberg, Jenny. "Afghan_Boys_Are_Prized,_So_Girls_Live_the_Part." The New York
Times, September 20, 2010.
Tsui, Amy. "In_Contraception,_the_U.S._is_Far_Behind_the_Developing_World." The
Baltimore Sun, September 26, 2010.
Friedman, Ann. "The_New_Workplace_Sexism." The American Prospect, August 2,
2010.
Bennett, Jessica. "The_Beauty_Advantage." Newsweek, July 19, 2010.
"Israel_Opening_More_Units_to_Women_Soldiers,_but_Will_They_See_Battle?" All
Headline News. November 18, 2010.
Dobie, Kathy. "The_Long_Road_Home:_Women_in_War." CNN. November 10, 2010.
"New_Study:_Men_Suffering_'Intimate_Terrorism'_by_Women_Partners." News and
Media Relations, Clarke University, Worcester, MA. August 12, 2010.
Campbell, Denis. "More_Than_40%_of_Domestic_Violence_Victims_are_Male,_Report
Reveals." The Guardian, September 5, 2010.
Belluck, Pam. "Group_Backs_Ritual_'Nick'_as_Female_Circumcision_Option." The
New York Times, May 6, 2010.
Nardini, Daniel. "Women in the Revolution." Lawndale Bilingual Newspapers,
September 9, 2010.
"Some_Mexican_Women_Lose_Right_to_Vote." MSNBC.com. January 27, 2008.
